<img alt="School Street, 1906, Boston.jpg" src="http://hawthornessevengables.com/images/School%20Street%2C%201906%2C%20Boston.jpg" width="320" height="322" class="mt-image-center" style="text-align: center; display: block; margin: 0 auto 20px;" /><div style="text-align: center;"><small><font color= "0000CC">School Street 1906</font></p>

<p><br />
Ordered that the street from Mr. Atherton Haughe's to Sentry Hill be laid out and kept open for ever.</p>

<p><br />
Boston Town Meeting, March 30, 1640</small></div></p>

