<p><br />
_____________________________________________________________________________</p>

<p><br />
<div style="text-align: center;"><font color="F70000"><big>Thomas St. John</big></font></div></p>

<p><br />
Thomas St. John's family is from Pittsfield in the Berkshire Hills of western Massachusetts. He graduated from Drew University, then lived in Montclair, New Jersey before moving to Boston, living on Commonwealth Avenue, Boylston Street, Hemenway Street, and Queensberry Streets, then in Cambridge, Massachusetts before removing to Brattleboro, Vermont. </p>

<p><br />
His has published with the University of Utah's "Western Humanities Review", the Ball State University "Forum", and the alternate news website "Counterpunch".</p>

<p><br />
<img alt="Captain John Bonner's Map Of Boston.png" src="http://hawthornessevengables.com/images/Captain%20John%20Bonner%27s%20Map%20Of%20Boston.png" width="508" height="236" class="mt-image-center" style="text-align: center; display: block; margin: 0 auto 20px;" /></p>
